==English==
===Etymology===
First recorded by the [[astronomer]] Jakob Bartsch in 1624, but probably created earlier by Petrus Plancius. From {{L.}} ''[[camelopardalis]]'', a "[[camelopard]], [[giraffe]]"

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Camelopardalis'''

#{{constellation}}: A faint [[circumpolar]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble a [[giraffe]].

